headline: Walmart may have had a strong Q3, but how are consumers feeling?
summary: Walmart (WMT) stock is getting a lift Thursday morning after the retail giant beat third quarter adjusted earnings ($0.62 per share vs. expectations of $0.60) and revenue estimates ($179.5 billion vs. expectations of $177.6 billion). The chain store raised its full-year forecast. Bianco Research President Jim Bianco, Great Hill Capital chairman and managing member Thomas Hayes, and Yahoo Finance senior reporter Brooke DiPalma all weigh in on Walmart's performance in comparison to competitor Target (TGT), Walmart's item pricing, and what the company's results represent about the state of the US consumer. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Opening Bid.
